commit.message: bump version to 0.18

Add support for 'name' option

'name' is a common options that should be supported by all
directives. It is implemented the same way as in Graphviz extension.

Sort options alphabetically

That way it will be easy to decide where to add new options.

tox: Restrict to Python 2.7

Currently tox.ini doesn't specify Python version. As tests doesn't
work with Python 3.x, running tox results in failure if Python 3.x is
installed.

This commit restricts Python to 2.7 and removes all comments from
tox.ini to keep it clean and simple.
Fix typo
bump version to 0.17.1

add LICENSE file (fixes #38)

It's probably lost while converting each sub-project to git.
bump version to 0.17

add `plantuml_syntax_error_image` option

To allow users to display images generated by plantuml when it
encounters an error.

catch IOError raised from PIL as well

fall back to builder.warn() if logging API doesn't exist

hopefully silence type mismatch warning of config value (fixes #29)
fix crash on loading corrupted image by PIL

Appears that builder.warn() has been removed.
bump version to 0.15
fix caption is not added correctly to underlying figure (fixes #25)
bump version to 0.14

refactor html visits to reduce code duplication

add support for sphinxcontrib-confluencebuilder

bump version to 0.13
clean up table styles

add html_format and latex_format options to override configuration per node

PlantUML supports ditaa diagrams. Unfortunately all output format options
are ignored, and only PNG is produced. This breaks both HTML and LaTeX mode.

Being able to override the output format for a specific diagram fixes the
problem.
bump version to 0.12

add svg_obj output format

This only renders SVG, inside <object/>, without any fallback. Closes #7.
Also partially handles #16.
